error: could not compile, possibly due to a mismatch in loss policy semantics.

The fixture attempts to create a LossyFormatExport with RefuseLoss policy, which
is a logical contradiction: LossyFormatExport is used for lossy transformations,
which should only occur under AllowNamedProjection or AllowLossWithReport policies.
RefuseLoss indicates the projection should refuse any loss, making lossy export
semantically invalid.

If compilation succeeds but this fixture is intended to fail, the issue may be
that the LossyFormatExport type does not validate the policy at construction time.
This would be a missing compile-fail validation.
